<paragraph id="8BA736E4F37A8A75FF11FBB5FD668264" blockId="5.[151,1437,1052,1619]" box="[151,701,1052,1079]" pageId="5" pageNumber="212">
<heading id="D0EF8188F37A8A75FF11FBB5FD668264" bold="true" box="[151,701,1052,1079]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="5" pageNumber="212" reason="1">
<emphasis id="B96CEAF6F37A8A75FF11FBB5FD668264" bold="true" box="[151,701,1052,1079]" pageId="5" pageNumber="212">
The 
<taxonomicName id="4C184D67F37A8A75FF4BFBB5FE188264" baseAuthorityName="Burmeister" baseAuthorityYear="1839" box="[205,451,1052,1079]" class="Insecta" family="Pseudostigmatidae" genus="Mecistogaster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="5" pageNumber="212" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amalia">
<emphasis id="B96CEAF6F37A8A75FF4BFBB5FE188264" bold="true" box="[205,451,1052,1079]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="212">Mecistogaster amalia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
of 
<bibRefCitation id="EF894B15F37A8A75FE6FFBB4FDB48264" author="Selys, M. E." box="[489,623,1052,1079]" pageId="5" pageNumber="212" pagination="9 - 27" refId="ref14250" refString="Selys, M. E. (1860) Synopsis des agrionines, Premiere Legion: Pseudostigma. Bulletins de l'Academie Royale, Belgique, 2 (10), 9 - 27." type="journal article" year="1860">Selys (1860</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EF894B15F37A8A75FDFAFBB4FD6E8264" author="Selys, M. E." box="[636,693,1052,1079]" pageId="5" pageNumber="212" pagination="1 - 233" refId="ref14284" refString="Selys, M. E. (1886) Revision der Synopsis des agrionines. Premiere partie Comprenar les legion: Pseudostigma, Podagrion, Platycnemis et Protoneura. Memmoire Couronnes et memoire pp l'Academie des sciences des letters et des beaux-arts de Belgique, 38 (4), 1 - 233." type="journal article" year="1886">1886</bibRefCitation>
)
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA736E4F37A8A75FF41FBE9FA9E8304" blockId="5.[151,1437,1052,1619]" pageId="5" pageNumber="212">
The first author to redescribe 
<taxonomicName id="4C184D67F37A8A75FD91FBEAFD508208" baseAuthorityName="Burmeister" baseAuthorityYear="1839" box="[535,651,1089,1115]" class="Insecta" family="Pseudostigmatidae" genus="Mecistogaster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="5" pageNumber="212" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amalia">
<emphasis id="B96CEAF6F37A8A75FD91FBEAFD508208" box="[535,651,1089,1115]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="212">M. amalia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
after 
<bibRefCitation id="EF894B15F37A8A75FD48FBE9FC478208" author="Burmeister, H. C." box="[718,924,1089,1115]" pageId="5" pageNumber="212" refId="ref12591" refString="Burmeister, H. C. (1839) Handbuch der Entomologie. Zweiter Band. Besondere Entomologie, Berlin, 1050 pp." type="book" year="1839">Burmeister (1839)</bibRefCitation>
was 
<bibRefCitation id="EF894B15F37A8A75FC5EFBE9FBBB8208" author="Selys, M. E." box="[984,1120,1089,1115]" pageId="5" pageNumber="212" pagination="9 - 27" refId="ref14250" refString="Selys, M. E. (1860) Synopsis des agrionines, Premiere Legion: Pseudostigma. Bulletins de l'Academie Royale, Belgique, 2 (10), 9 - 27." type="journal article" year="1860">Selys (1860</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EF894B15F37A8A75FBEAFBE9FB73820F" author="Selys, M. E." box="[1132,1192,1089,1116]" pageId="5" pageNumber="212" pagination="1 - 233" refId="ref14284" refString="Selys, M. E. (1886) Revision der Synopsis des agrionines. Premiere partie Comprenar les legion: Pseudostigma, Podagrion, Platycnemis et Protoneura. Memmoire Couronnes et memoire pp l'Academie des sciences des letters et des beaux-arts de Belgique, 38 (4), 1 - 233." type="journal article" year="1886">1886</bibRefCitation>
), based on specimens from his own collection and that of Hagen, without seeing the 
<typeStatus id="54A38846F37A8A75FCDCFBCDFC1B822C" box="[858,960,1125,1151]" pageId="5" pageNumber="212">holotype</typeStatus>
. The main characters in Selys’ description are: pseudostigma in both wings with 5 
<emphasis id="B96CEAF6F37A8A75FDCEFB21FD8A82F0" bold="true" box="[584,593,1161,1187]" pageId="5" pageNumber="212">-</emphasis>
7 cells and 1 or 2 cells in the row below, on adults black, and yellowish, dark brown on young; apex of wings of adult fully hyaline, of semi-adult infuscate, and milky on young; median lobe of prothorax with two large rounded reddish markings; two yellowish humeral lines originating in opposite directions, inner one touching the anterior border, but not the sinus, and outer one touching the sinus, but not the anterior border; mesepimeron reddish-brown; lower part of thorax with a large black median stripe not surrounded by black. According to 
<bibRefCitation id="EF894B15F37A8A75FEB7FA95FE628304" author="Selys, M. E." box="[305,441,1341,1367]" pageId="5" pageNumber="212" pagination="9 - 27" refId="ref14250" refString="Selys, M. E. (1860) Synopsis des agrionines, Premiere Legion: Pseudostigma. Bulletins de l'Academie Royale, Belgique, 2 (10), 9 - 27." type="journal article" year="1860">Selys (1860</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EF894B15F37A8A75FE42FA95FDDB830B" author="Selys, M. E." box="[452,512,1341,1368]" pageId="5" pageNumber="212" pagination="1 - 233" refId="ref14284" refString="Selys, M. E. (1886) Revision der Synopsis des agrionines. Premiere partie Comprenar les legion: Pseudostigma, Podagrion, Platycnemis et Protoneura. Memmoire Couronnes et memoire pp l'Academie des sciences des letters et des beaux-arts de Belgique, 38 (4), 1 - 233." type="journal article" year="1886">1886</bibRefCitation>
), the species occurs in 
<collectingRegion id="49DCF806F37A8A75FC87FA95FC7D8304" box="[769,934,1341,1367]" country="Brazil" name="Rio de Janeiro" pageId="5" pageNumber="212">Rio de Janeiro</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="49DCF806F37A8A75FC37FA95FBFE8304" box="[945,1061,1341,1367]" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="5" pageNumber="212">São Paulo</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="49DCF806F37A8A75FBB6FA95FBAA8304" box="[1072,1137,1341,1367]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="5" pageNumber="212">Bahia</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion id="49DCF806F37A8A75FB2EFA95FA998304" box="[1192,1346,1341,1367]" country="Brazil" name="Minas Gerais" pageId="5" pageNumber="212">Minas Gerais</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C302656FF37A8A75FF41FAC9FB608000" pageId="5" pageNumber="212" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BA736E4F37A8A75FF41FAC9FB608000" blockId="5.[151,1437,1052,1619]" pageId="5" pageNumber="212">
This description is quite different from that of 
<bibRefCitation id="EF894B15F37A8A75FD5BFAC9FC768328" author="Burmeister, H. C." box="[733,941,1377,1403]" pageId="5" pageNumber="212" refId="ref12591" refString="Burmeister, H. C. (1839) Handbuch der Entomologie. Zweiter Band. Besondere Entomologie, Berlin, 1050 pp." type="book" year="1839">Burmeister (1839)</bibRefCitation>
by the whole mesepimeron reddish-brown, as well as similar color on the curved marking on the median lobe of the prothorax whereas in the 
<taxonomicName id="4C184D67F37A8A75FB61FA2EFA8183CC" baseAuthorityName="Burmeister" baseAuthorityYear="1839" box="[1255,1370,1413,1439]" class="Insecta" family="Pseudostigmatidae" genus="Mecistogaster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="5" pageNumber="212" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amalia">
<emphasis id="B96CEAF6F37A8A75FB61FA2EFA8183CC" box="[1255,1370,1413,1439]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="212">M. amalia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<typeStatus id="54A38846F37A8A75FAE7FA2DFF1C8390" pageId="5" pageNumber="212">holotype</typeStatus>
these areas are supposedly bronze black. Another difference is the median black stripe on the venter in Selys’ specimens, and white in 
<bibRefCitation id="EF894B15F37A8A75FE32FA65FD4383B4" author="Burmeister, H. C." box="[436,664,1485,1511]" pageId="5" pageNumber="212" refId="ref12591" refString="Burmeister, H. C. (1839) Handbuch der Entomologie. Zweiter Band. Besondere Entomologie, Berlin, 1050 pp." type="book" year="1839">Burmeister’s (1839)</bibRefCitation>
description. 
<bibRefCitation id="EF894B15F37A8A75FCA8FA65FC6383B4" author="Selys, M. E." box="[814,952,1485,1511]" pageId="5" pageNumber="212" pagination="9 - 27" refId="ref14250" refString="Selys, M. E. (1860) Synopsis des agrionines, Premiere Legion: Pseudostigma. Bulletins de l'Academie Royale, Belgique, 2 (10), 9 - 27." type="journal article" year="1860">Selys (1860</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EF894B15F37A8A75FC43FA65FC2583BB" author="Selys, M. E." box="[965,1022,1485,1512]" pageId="5" pageNumber="212" pagination="1 - 233" refId="ref14284" refString="Selys, M. E. (1886) Revision der Synopsis des agrionines. Premiere partie Comprenar les legion: Pseudostigma, Podagrion, Platycnemis et Protoneura. Memmoire Couronnes et memoire pp l'Academie des sciences des letters et des beaux-arts de Belgique, 38 (4), 1 - 233." type="journal article" year="1886">1886</bibRefCitation>
) comments that the identification is very easy because of the reddish-brown mesepimeron, which is black in all other 
<taxonomicName id="4C184D67F37A8A75FBAFFA5AFB138058" authorityName="Rambur" authorityYear="1842" box="[1065,1224,1522,1547]" class="Insecta" family="Pseudostigmatidae" genus="Mecistogaster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="5" pageNumber="212" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96CEAF6F37A8A75FBAFFA5AFB138058" box="[1065,1224,1522,1547]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="212">Mecistogaster</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It is reasonable to assume that Selys’ description (1860, 1886) of 
<taxonomicName id="4C184D67F37A8A75FD36F9BEFCFE807C" baseAuthorityName="Burmeister" baseAuthorityYear="1839" box="[688,805,1557,1583]" class="Insecta" family="Pseudostigmatidae" genus="Mecistogaster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="5" pageNumber="212" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amalia">
<emphasis id="B96CEAF6F37A8A75FD36F9BEFCFE807C" box="[688,805,1557,1583]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="212">M. amalia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and not that of 
<bibRefCitation id="EF894B15F37A8A75FC5BF9BDFB77807C" author="Burmeister, H. C." box="[989,1196,1557,1583]" pageId="5" pageNumber="212" refId="ref12591" refString="Burmeister, H. C. (1839) Handbuch der Entomologie. Zweiter Band. Besondere Entomologie, Berlin, 1050 pp." type="book" year="1839">Burmeister (1839)</bibRefCitation>
has been used by all subsequent authors. This description fits well with that of 
<taxonomicName id="4C184D67F37A8A75FCA7F992FC4F8000" baseAuthorityName="Burmeister" baseAuthorityYear="1839" box="[801,916,1593,1619]" class="Insecta" family="Pseudostigmatidae" genus="Mecistogaster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="5" pageNumber="212" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amalia">
<emphasis id="B96CEAF6F37A8A75FCA7F992FC4F8000" box="[801,916,1593,1619]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="212">M. amalia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<typeStatus id="54A38846F37A8A75FC1DF991FC2F8000" box="[923,1012,1593,1619]" pageId="5" pageNumber="212">neotype</typeStatus>
described herein.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
